website_summaries.verdict: Whether you want to mix it with kibble or your pooch will only eat canned food, this is a good option for dogs on a diet.
pros: A low-fat canned dog food with a flavor many dog owners say that their pets love
Contains ingredients that are easy to digest, such as rice
cons: Consistency is somewhat thick and "clumpy" for canned food – some consumers wish it had more gravy

customer_reviews.title: Yuck!
customer_reviews.text: Our pittie has gained a lot of weight since he was neutered at age 9, so I am shopping around for a decent weight control dog food. Trust me on this, this is not the one. This stuff smells horrible and has a thin, sticky texture completely unlike regular Pedigree chopped ground dinners. He will eat it, but he gives me a wicked side-eye the entire time he's doing so. Poor Boo, I'm not going to force him to eat this stuff.
customer_reviews.author: D. J. Taylor

customer_reviews.title: Low fat content
customer_reviews.text: The main reason I bought this dog food is the low fat content. My dog recently has had several flare ups of pancreatitis. The vet gave us a brand of low fat dog food to deal with the pancreatitis. This brand is sold by Amazon, too, but the price is just too high. Sorry puppy. You got stuck with the cheap alternative. My dog eats this food with hesitation and it smells ok to me. I just wish Pedigree would offer more than two flavors of the low fat food.
customer_reviews.author: HappyGoLucky

customer_reviews.title: Works for our dog
customer_reviews.text: My dog requires a low fat dog food because she has had a few bouts of pancreatitis. Normally, I make her food from scratch, but it's not always practical when we're traveling. She likes this food, and so far, she has had no issues with pancreatitis when we've given it to her while on vacation.
customer_reviews.author: knitbunnie

customer_reviews.title: Tasty weight management wet dog food
customer_reviews.text: My older miniature poodle was getting a bit over weight, so I switched to this product. She is sort of picky in food so I held my breath when I introduced Pedigree Weight Management Adult wet food. She now runs to eat her meal and finishes her portion in one time. Many other weight control dog foods have sat for hours before she would finally eat. I am very pleased that she enjoys eating again and the price is very affordable.

customer_reviews.title: My used to be Fat Dog LOVES it!
